				<h3>European Business Desk</h3>
                <p>Europe Union (EU) is one of the largest trading partners of India accounting for approximately eighteen percent of Indian export and approximately twelve percent of imports from EU countries. European Union is a Customs Union permitting free movement of goods and services, thereby making the European Union a single common market for Indian investments to Company formation in Europe.</p>
                <p>In this respect, as a Customs Union, the European Union provides an attractive destination for outbound investment by Indian companies in the European Union member countries and inbound investment by companies in European Union member countries to India.</p>
				<p>Some additional points that make the European Union an attractive destination for investments are technology, know-how, the possibility of acquiring niche brands, unique manufacturing capability, automation, access to developed economies of Europe with a higher per capita income, political stability, stable tax, financial, and regulatory regimes.	</p>
				<p>With experience of more than 25 years in financial, management, and legal consulting, ASC Group has a strong network of business solutions thus helping companies/investors to expand and strengthen their business in the EU. In the EU, ASC Group works with our experienced and reputed network of contacts, thus enabling ASC Group to provide one-stop solutions for Company formation in Europe / executing investment in the EU.	</p>
				<p>In the European Union, ASC Group’s spectrum of services includes market entry strategy, Mergers & Acquisitions, Management Consulting, Strategy Consulting, Market Research, Legal Advisory, Tax, and Regulatory Services, Audit, Assurance Services, Company formation in Europe, Certification Services, Transfer Pricing, Corporate Restructuring, Drafting and Documentation, Corporate Compliance, Enterprise Risk Management, Business Process Improvement, Transaction Support Services, Manpower Outsourcing and other consultancy services to companies and business entities willing to invest/Company formation in Europe.				</p>
                <br>
                <h3>Market Entry Strategy Services				</h3>
                <p>Our Market Entry Strategy practice provides consulting services for Company formation in Europe and assists in devising appropriate market entry strategies. This includes:</p>
				<ul style="margin-left: 40px;">
					<li>Options for entry (both equity and non-equity forms)
					</li>
					<li>Challenges and risks associated with different entry options
					</li>
					<li>Evaluation of the regulatory environment, tax, and other government incentives
					</li>
					<li>Screening of partners/acquisition targets
					</li>
					<li>Feasibility study and location analysis (including the availability of tax and other government incentives available in various states)
					</li>
					<li>Analysis of tax-efficient funding structures and repatriation strategies
					</li>
				</ul>
                <br>
               
                <h3>Legal Services</h3>
                <div class="row">
                    <div class="col-md-12">
                        <p>The Deals team offers services across the deal continuum including advisory on Mergers, Acquisitions, Divestitures, Joint Ventures, Spin-offs, and Strategic Alliances.</p>
                     
						<ul style="margin-left: 40px;">
							<li><b>Corporate finance: </b> provides complete deal advisory services including target identification, target screening, developing transaction strategy, working capital management and restructuring advisory, negotiation, and documentation drafting support and assistance in transaction closure
							</li>
							<li><b>Due diligence:</b>  includes financial, tax, commercial, operational, legal, forensics, and HR operations analysis. Our due diligence team also carries out a primary and secondary credentials review on the potential JV partner / Acquisition target
							</li>
							<li><b>Valuation:</b> services include business and asset valuations for transactions, tax, dispute, financial reporting, governance, and regulatory needs. Specific services include purchase price allocations, independent expert reports, and fair opinions
							</li>
							<li><b>Post-merger integration:</b> services help identify positive revenue, cost, core synergies, and opportunities across all functions in an organization to maximize cum unlock integration value
							</li>
						</ul>
                    </div>

                </div>
